## SECTION 6 — IPFS / PINATA PIPELINE

From `metadata.py`: [raw.githubusercontent](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/welshDog/BROskiPets-LLM-dNFT/main/metadata.py)

### 6.1 Upload Pipeline
```
generate_metadata(state) 
  → hash state (SHA-256)
  → check Redis cache (idempotency — skip re-upload if state unchanged)
  → upload to Pinata /pinning/pinFileToIPFS
  → cache CID in Redis (7-day TTL)
  → return CID → contract.evolve(tokenId, CID, stage)
```

### 6.2 Pinata API Endpoints Required
| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `/pinning/pinFileToIPFS` | POST | Upload image assets |
| `/pinning/pinJSONToIPFS` | POST | Upload metadata JSON |
| IPFS Gateway | GET | `https://gateway.pinata.cloud/ipfs/{CID}` |

### 6.3 Image Asset Structure (Planned)
```
ipfs://EEPVengers/{pet_id}/{stage_name}.png
  stages: baby | young | trained | elite | legendary | quantum
  per pet: 6 images × 78 EEPs = 468 total image assets needed
```

